New Records: Harry Kane marked his 100th senior international appearance with both goals in England's 2-0 victory over Finland.
Harry Kane took his England tally to a record-extending 68 goals.
Key Match Events: Harry Kane scored the opening goal with a dipping right-footed strike in the 57th minute.
Harry Kane scored his second goal in the 76th minute, sweeping in another right-footed effort.
Harry Kane had a first-half header ruled out for offside.
Lukas Hradecky made several fine saves to deny Harry Kane.
Harry Kane was given a standing ovation when he was substituted in the 80th minute.
Pre-Game Insights: Harry Kane received a golden cap before kick-off and sported a pair of dazzling golden boots.
Post-Match Reflections: England's win was their second under interim manager Lee Carsley after the away victory over Ireland on Saturday.
England's win puts them joint top of their Nations League group with Greece.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was played on a wet London night.

Trent Alexander-Arnold was rated as England’s best player with five or six stunning passes that carved the Finns open and got an assist for one of his more routine passes thanks to Kane’s brilliant strike.
